{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ed514a82-92c8-4e4b-b158-89229b49104e","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest runner/adapter by default.** Your test assembly is now a standalone executable using Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) only — it no longer ships the VSTest adapter hooks that `vstest.console` needs to discover tests.\n\n### How to fix\n\n**Option A — Switch your CI to `dotnet test` (recommended):**\n\n```bash\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj\n```\n\n`dotnet test` in modern .NET SDKs natively supports MTP-based test projects.\n\n**Option B — Run the test executable directly:**\n\n```bash\ndotnet build && ./bin/Debug/net8.0/TestProject\n```\n\nMTP test projects are self-contained executables.\n\n**Option C — Re-enable the VSTest adapter** (if you must keep `vstest.console`):\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform>false</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\nThis opts back into the classic VSTest adapter, but you lose MTP features.\n\n**Option A is the recommended path forward** — it aligns with where the MSTest ecosystem is heading.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bef6e7e2-af13-4294-8eff-238add9554c6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a known breaking change in MSTest.Sdk. Let me explain what happened.\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0, the SDK uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) by default instead of VSTest. In MSTest.Sdk 3.x, there was a property `EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform` that defaulted to `true` but you could set it to `false` to keep VSTest compatibility. The test assemblies built with MTP are standalone executables and don't produce the VSTest-compatible adapter hooks that `vstest.console` needs to discover tests.\n\nActually, let me be more precise. \n\nIn version 3.x, the VSTest adapter was still included by default even though MTP was the primary runner, so `vstest.console` could still discover and run tests. But in version 4.x, the VSTest compatibility layer was removed entirely—the SDK now exclusively uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform, which means `vstest.console` can no longer find your tests because the necessary adapter isn't there anymore. To work around this, you'd need to either migrate your CI pipeline to use the new testing platform or explicitly add back the VSTest adapter dependency. So the core issue is that MSTest.Sdk 4.x completely removed the VSTest adapter layer, meaning tests are now standalone executables built on Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Since `vstest.console` depends on those adapters to discover tests, it can't find anything anymore. The workaround is either switching to `dotnet test` which has native MTP support, or disabling the Testing Platform entry point and explicitly adding back the MSTest VSTest adapter package.","outputTokens":1091,"requestId":"1BD5:4309A:BD008C:D65A6E:6A03F351"},"id":"2d39a391-9498-410b-a915-cd1359337d29","timestamp":"2026-05-13T03:43:36.747Z","parentId":"5e24716c-cbf5-47de-b8cc-247fbf8851f3"}
